/>&gt; <br />&gt; To make threaded apps very compatible:<br />&gt; getpid() could return just the bottom 16 bits to make userspace<br />&gt; even more happy. Then a gettid() function gets the whole 32 bits.<br />&gt; Normal kill() handles both just fine.<br /><br />Works for me.<br /><br />&gt; Symmetry requires numbering unthreaded processes from 0x10000.<br />&gt; They still show up with low numbers and can be killed with the<br />&gt; low numbers.<br />&gt; <br />&gt; That gets rid of some special case code for thread #1.<br /><br />Sure, I can live with this (in fact I think I prefer it to my original<br />setup). <br /><br />Now, does anybody actually want to _implement_ this?<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
